reviews.text:
Atmosphere looks good and clean, so I thought. The clean spoons still had dirty food on them, I didn't even want to eat my food after that. The soup i order had too much vinegar or acidity, I only ate one spoonful. The gyro sandwich was OK, but the pita bread here is like a loaf, its way to big and thick. I wish the sandwiches had some other veggie than onions and meat.

I wouldn't return. Its a Saturday night and this place has been empty from 6-8p. That says alit about what people think about this place. But go try it for yourself.
They have the food out pretty fast, but fresh and is absolutely scrumptious and flavorful! The desserts are very delicious as well.

I went here for the first time accompanied by someone that has experience with the food. For other first timers: you go in and order at a counter, they'll give you your cups and then you pick a table and they'll call your name when your food is ready. They have the menu on the wall but also hand held sheets so you can stand to the side and make up your mind. The food was good, the men making the plates were friendly and you get plenty for your money (I ate twice from my portion). Our only small issue was that the lady that took our order didn't want the experienced person to order lamb. Maybe they were out or running low, but he gave his order and she kept repeating a version of: pork is our traditional meat, pork is the traditional order, etc , and by the third time she said it, he gave in and ordered the pork, then during the meal he said that having had them both now, he should have insisted on the lamb. It won't keep us from returning, it was just a little odd.

Pros: large portions, highly affordable, delicious savory and sweet food, lots of seating, large menu selections, cool building
Cons: not much parking

Great prices, delicious food! Best Greek I've ever had! Even to this day! Everything on the menu is delicious, and I mean EVERYTHING (why yes, I HAVE tried it all). Definitely try the desserts as they rotate their selection almost every time.

A truly exceptional dining experience! Every dish was a masterpiece of flavor and presentation, with fresh, high-quality ingredients that shone through in every bite. The lady at the register was a fill-in,  normaly not in front, but she was incredibly knowledgeable and attentive, making sure every question was answered, with no rushed feeling. The ambiance was warm and inviting, and we left feeling completely satisfied - this is definitely a must-visit for anyone seeking a memorable culinary journey!

editorial_summary.overview: Popular, warm Mediterranean joint serving a variety of gyro sandwiches, fresh pita & mezze platters.
